In [26]:
sns.scatterplot(x='total', y='alcohol', data=df)
plt.xlabel('Total Crashes')
plt.ylabel('Alcohol Involvement (Percentage)')
plt.title('Total Crashes vs. Alcohol Involvement')
plt.show()

Inference: There seems to be a discernible positive correlation between the total number of crashes and the percentage of alcohol involvement in car accidents.
